<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-04-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-04-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="189" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d189">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Seward</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Stockton</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 13.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                    State</hi>,<lb/><placeName><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-04-30"><hi rend="italic">April</hi> 30, 1861</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: An instruction, numbered 2, and dated the
                            29th instant, has been addressed to your successor, Mr. King, of which,
                            as it relates to a subject of present moment, I have deemed it expedient
                            to send you a transcript, which you will find enclosed. It is thought
                            desirable that the views therein expressed should be communicated to the
                            Papal government without delay.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer><signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">John P. Stockton</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., Rome</hi>.</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>